name: Maze Arenas
description:
Another map on which you can conduct PVP battles in Terraria. There are 6 different arenas on the Maze Arenas map at once. Each of the arenas has a unique design, structure and hazards.

What's on the map
	Sinister Arena (best played at night)
	hell arena
	Lizard Arena
	underground arena
	teleport arena

name: Death Arena
description:
Another map sharpened for PvP battles. The author has created as many as 20 different arenas and 88 classes, it is best to play 2x2 or 3x3. This map has strict rules of the game, if you want good battles, then it is better not to break them.

Rules of the game
	Don't break any blocks
	You and your friends must have the same type of equipment
	Some cards have a specific item that can be found in a glass chest. Everyone can use items from the chest, but only 1 item can be taken.
	Before starting a battle in the arenas, all players must have 400 HP and 200 mana.
	You cannot change accessories in the middle of the game (in the Arena)
	Some classes have style items and you must place them in style slots
	Do not interact with any NPC other than the nurse
	After using a class, you must put it in this class chest

name: Hunger Games Card
description: PvP map for 2 or more players, there is a lot of scattered loot in this world. But at the same time, there are a bunch of different traps, in general, real hunger games for Terraria. Invite your friends and find out which one of you is the real mockingjay

name: Counter Strike
description:
Let's combine two popular games and have some Counter Strike-style fun with Terraria's game mechanics? The task of the map is simple, but not without peculiarities. The terrorists must get to the dungeon, kill the Skeletron and find the Mechanic in the Dungeon, buy wires and a wrench, and then try to connect a lever near the tower to explosives and, accordingly, blow up this tower.It's simple, right? The Counter-Terrarists have a simpler task, but no less important - while the Terrarists make their little journey for copper cable to hand it over to a collection point for non-ferrous metals by the wires to the Mechanic in Dungeon, the Counter-Terrarians must prepare to meet the “guests”. How the preparations will take place - it all depends on your imagination and the time that you will have from the beginning of the game to the moment of meeting.

The card is designed for the number of players from two to eight people. Best of all, of course, eight, since there are 4 classes in the game and the most interesting game will turn out just with the full complement.

Player Classes:
	Demoman
	attack plane
	Sniper
	Heavy infantry
